node.text:
29299 Maple Ave, Trappe, MD 21673
$675,000, 8 bd, 4 ba, 6,881 sqft

This property has many possibilities. As is, it could be a home with abundant charm, your own in-town estate with housing for a caretaker or with rental income (second house needs work), and places for all your cars, boats, and other toys (if some existing buildings had been torn down this potential would have been limited). Alternately, there are a minimum of 2 building lots that could be more rental property or subdivided and sold. It also has B & B potential. If you are only interested in the house and pool, a local farmer is interested in purchasing the back part of the property and you would still have the area to the east of the driveway that could be sold.  Circa 1870..... 2 Homes on one property!!! If the elegance of antique houses with spacious rooms, high ceilings, and abundant charm delight then your in luck! Unusual 3 story construction, Slate shingles & copper metal, double  interior & exterior brick, most exterior walls two course brick with an air layer between, granite thresholds and window sills. Circle driveway, Large wrap around Mahogany porch with portico. Mansard roof = more room on 3rd floor. High ceilings, transom windows, beautiful moldings, heart pine floors, beautiful halls & staircase to 3rd floor, 9 fireplaces - 5 with vent-free gas logs. 

Listed by:
Brett Schrader
Taylor Properties 301-970-2447

node.text:
The Webb Horton House, is an ornate 40-room mansion in Middletown, New York, United States, designed by local architect Frank Lindsey. Built 1902-1906 as a private residence, since the late 1940s it has been part of the campus of SUNY Orange. This building is now known as Morrison Hall, after the last private owner, and houses the college's main administrative offices. A nearby service complex has also been kept and is used for classrooms and other college functions. Photo by @samanthassamantiques

node.text:
711 Holston Ave, Bristol, TN 37620
$599,985, 5 bd, 3 ba, 5,030 sqft

Here is a rare opportunity to own one of Bristol's crown jewels.  711 Holston Ave is a graceful combination of historic charm coupled with modern updates. You will appreciate the quality of craftsmanship and attention to detail from the moment you step foot on the property.  This amazing 5 bedroom, 3 bath home offers over 5000 sq ft of living space.  This property was the first in the neighborhood when construction began in 1905 for Judge Robert Burrow.  It remained well cared for in the Burrow family until 1979.  In recent years the home has seen major updates with all new plumbing, electrical, roof, HVAC systems, and more.  All completed while preserving the original woodwork and character in the home. You are greeted with a grand foyer and towering intricate staircase. The large scale of the rooms makes entertaining easy in the living and dining rooms. The farmhouse-style kitchen has been updated with granite counters, an island, and an antique gas stove. There is a terrific office with private exterior access, a den, a full bath, and laundry rounding out the main level. 

Listed by:
Josh Taylor
Remax Results Bristol 423-793-1130

node.text:
5328 State Route 70, Jonesville, VA 24263
$169,000, 4 bd, 2 ba, 3,603 sqft

The William C. and Mary E. Cox Home is available for the first time in five decades. The stately 2 story home built circa 1919 is nestled on 17 acres of land and has picturesque mountain views. It has 4 bedrooms, 2 full baths, updated kitchen with hickory cabinets, formal dining room with built in china cabinets, 2 family rooms and a breathtaking wooden staircase in the center hall. There are 7 fireplaces adorned with beautiful mantelpieces . Original woodwork, doors and hardware are present throughout the house. This property also has a fenced in backyard and a garden shed. For the gardening enthusiast, the yard has a fenced garden plot, plum trees, hydrangea and snoball bushes. Don't miss this opportunity to make this your home.All information taken from third party and tax records. Buyer and buyers broker to verify.

Listed by:
Julia Estes
Jones Property Group

node.text:
109 S Hamilton St, Poughkeepsie, NY 12601
$450,000, 7 bd, 3 ba, 5,952 sqft

A meandering path and stone clad steps lead the way to this magnificent early 1900's Victorian style Estate home. A spacious veranda welcome you and is the perfect respite on a breezy summer day. You will be in awe of the woodwork, columns, molding, corbels and more as you stroll around outside and inside this home. Large wooden double doors open to a vestibule where an additional set of double doors lead you on a journey inside where you'll feel as though you've traveled back in time gazing at the skilled craftsmanship and detail expressed in this home. Incredible wooden arches and original historic details are found throughout. The main great room has an ornate wooden fireplace and leaded glass bookcases. Warm hardwood floors carry you through formal and informal spaces separated by pocket doors. A formal living room and formal dining room both have original fireplaces with glass tile surrounds and carved wooden details and mantels. Period lighting and sconces add to the allure. A butler's pantry leads you into the vintage kitchen with dumbwaiter at the rear of the house and access to the spacious backyard. A powder room completes the main floor. 

Listing by:
Houlihan Lawrence Inc. Lg 845-473-9770
Katherine(Kaye) Saglibene

node.text:
1203 Grove Ter, Dubuque, IA 52001
$799,000, 5 bd, 4 ba, 6,308 sqft

Dubuque's Finest! Grand Victorian "Painted Lady" on bluff with fabulous city and river views. Built by Dubuque's first lumber baron, this home is rich in cherry, walnut, maple & pine woods. Home completely rehabbed in 1992, newer slate roof, copper gutters and fabulous landscaping surround this magnificent home. The beautiful wrap around front porch invites you to watch sunrises, and the city lights in the evening. The current owners have done many quality upgrades and their pride shines thru. Four grand fireplaces, master suite with 17x15 sitting room & 14x10 walk thru closet. Beautiful tiled updated master bath - 18x32 Billiard room can be 5th bedroom.

Listed by:
Deb Hooks
EXIT Realty Dubuque

node.text:
Before and After of the Laurietta House built in 1825 in Mississippi. 
When high school sweethearts Maria Teresa "Tere" and William "Mac" Thomas, married for 39 years, began searching for a getaway near their hometown of New Iberia, Louisiana, Mac, an oil executive, had a hunting camp in mind. After a broker showed him the 680-acre property with rolling, wooded hills and a three-acre lake, he loved everything ... except the broken-down shell of a house that came with the parcel. "It was nothing that a match couldn't cure," jokes Mac. And so began what Tere calls Mac's "gift of love," a three-year gut renovation. Photo by Björn Wallander

node.text: The Hegeler Carus Mansion, located at 1307 Seventh Street in La Salle, Illinois is one of the Midwest's great Second Empire structures. Completed in 1876 for Edward C. Hegeler, a partner in the nearby Matthiessen Hegeler Zinc Company, the mansion was designed in 1874 by noted Chicago architect William W. Boyington. The mansion is now owned and operated by the Hegeler Carus Foundation, and is open to the public. It was designated a National Historic Landmark in 2007. Photo by @stamps.on.my.passport
